Instead of an overworked father leaving his child to cook in the car, what about an earthquake that ends up having the same effect? Say, causing extended starvation of the child?<br>
<br>
Could God provide manna to children caught in an earthquake, thereby preventing them from starving? Have you ever heard of such a miracle occurring on a regular basis (i.e. whenever an earthquake occurs)?<br>
