How on earth was that baby's death free will? The father certainly didn't CHOOSE to forget his baby in the car. <br>
All a god would've had to do is spark a glimmer of *something* in that father's mind, that would remind him that his infant was in the car. All a god would've had to do, as someone mentioned, was tweaked someone's mind to peek in the car while walking by. <br>
He can make his face appear in potato chips, but he can't intervene in something as terrifyingly horrible as this death? And countless others?<br>
And if it's &quot;god's plan&quot; that that baby was to &quot;belong in heaven&quot;, and not on earth, then don't you think that god could've chosen a slightly better method of getting him to heaven? Rather than slowly cooking him to death? Maybe a painless SIDS death? What made god decide to make a helpless infant suffer an agonizing death? <br>
Answers please. And we've already determined it has nothing to do with &quot;free will&quot; because there was nothing for the father to &quot;choose&quot; in this case. <br>
Emmy<br>
